TE.tryCatch takes the thunk plus an onError narrower. Here unknown maps to a tagged FileErr so downstream consumers can match on _tag.

```typescript
import * as TE from "fp-ts/TaskEither";
import { readFile } from "node:fs/promises";

type FileErr = { readonly _tag: "FileErr"; readonly cause: unknown };

const load = (p: string): TE.TaskEither<FileErr, string> =>
